      #card-content-1.assignment-card.card
        .assignment-title.col-12
          .col-10
            p.assignment-title-type Chapter Assignment 2 / HTML&CSS
            p.assignment-title-focus Please check this file for me, thanks!
          .assignment-more-icon.col-2
            i.material-icons more_vert
        .assignment-content
          .assignment-content-header.col-12
            .user.row-custom.align-items-center
              img.user-image(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hexschool/webLayoutTraining1st/master/week5/emilywang.jpeg', alt='user-pic')
              .user-data
                p.user-name Emily Wang
                p.user-reply-time 10:38 AM (4 hours ago)
          .assignment-content-body.col-12
            p
              | Hi Teacher, the attached file is my homework of chapter 2. And here comes a question: Why in the following code the
              | height of the 
              span.focus-string div
              |   is bigger than the height of the 
              span.focus-string img
              |  ? There is a gap below the image, but it doesn’t seems to be
              |                     a
              |                     padding/margin.
            p What is the gap or extra space below image?
          .assignment-content-footer
            button.attachment-button.d-flex.align-items-center(type='button')
              i.material-icons attach_file
              span HW-2-David.zip
        .assignment-content
          .assignment-content-header.col-12
            .user.row-custom.align-items-center
              img.user-image(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hexschool/webLayoutTraining1st/master/week5/andychen.jpeg', alt='user-pic')
              .user-data
                p.user-name Andy Chen
                p.user-reply-time 13:24 AM (1 hours ago)
          .assignment-content-body.col-12
            p
              | Hi David, by default, an image is rendered inline, like a letter so it sits on the same line that a, b, c and d sit on.
              | There is space below that line for the descenders you find on letters like g, j, p and q.
            br
            p You can:
            br
            ul
              li
                | adjust the 
                span.focus-string vertical-align
                |  of the image to position it elsewhere (e.g. the middle)
              li
                | change the 
                span.focus-string display
                |  so it isn’t inline.
      .actions-area.row-custom.justify-content-between
        .actions-area-icons
          i.material-icons chevron_left
          i.material-icons chevron_right
        ul
          li.actions-area-buttons.d-flex
            button.mark-button.d-flex.align-items-center(type='button') Mark as read
            button.reply-button.d-flex.align-items-center(type='button') Reply